[1] Cholera - Uganda
Date: Tue, 21 Sep 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and The Monitor (Kampala) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200409201484.html>

Cholera Hits Kasese
-------------------
A fresh cholera outbreak has hit some parts of the district as rains
increase, health officials have confirmed. In a press release, the district
councilor representing Maliba sub-county, Mr Saulo Maate, said 7 cases had
been reported in the past few days in his sub-county alone.
Maate said 5 cases were reported in Mubuku village and 2 others in
Nyakakindo village. Maate said all the 7 were admitted to Kilembe Mines
Hospital, where they are recovering steadily. He called for the
intervention of the district authorities before the situation runs out of
hand. The district disease surveillance officer, Mr Pedson Butala,
confirmed the outbreak when contacted on Sun 19 Sep 2004, but said there
were 2 cases.
Butala attributed the outbreak to poor sanitary conditions in affected
areas. He said there was need for more anti-cholera drugs, which he said
were in short supply in the district.
[byline: Michael Karugaba]
******
[2] Cholera - Sierra Leone
Date: Tue, 21 Sep 2004
From: Charles Chambers <cchambers@cdc.gov>

The latest update has some confusing numbers. In the update on Sierra Leone
it states that they have had 15 deaths in Freetown. In an IRIN New.org
article, dated 27 Aug 2004, it stated there were 40 deaths just in that
month.
<http://www.irinnews.org/report.asp?ReportID=3D42913&SelectRegion=3DWest_Africa&SelectCountry=3DSIERRA_LEONE>
"We have been cholera-free since 1999," Alhassan Seisay, the director of
disease prevention, said by telephone from Freetown. "But since 6 Aug 2004
authorities have recorded 374 cases of the disease and 40 deaths."
[ProMED-mail appreciates the contributor's comment. It is possible that one
set of numbers represents the country as a whole as compared to the smaller
set, which appears to be from one particular medical center. - Mod.LL]
--
Charles Chambers
CDC Data Analyst
<cchambers@cdc.gov>
